# TrainDiary — React Native Mobile Dev Context

> **Purpose:** This document gives a new agent (or developer) everything needed to build the React Native mobile app from scratch, using the existing backend API without modification.

---

## 1. Project Overview

**App Name:** TrainDiary (branded as "Ascent | Performance Elite")  
**Purpose:** A premium fitness tracking app — workout logging, nutrition tracking, hydration, macro goals, body metrics and monthly progress summaries.  
**Web frontend repo:** `d:\Code\Web\traindiary-new-frontend` (Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS v4)  
**Backend repo:** `d:\Code\Web\traindiary-refactor-backend` (Next.js API routes on Vercel)  
**Live backend URL:** `https://traindiary-refactor-backend.vercel.app`  
**Design language:** Dark mode, ultra-minimal, premium — black backgrounds, blue primary (`#3b82f6`), bold italic uppercase typography.

---

